{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":5},{"title":2,"date":3,"citation":4},"Jewish inscriptions of Western Europe","1993","\u003Cspan>D. Noy, \u003Ci>Jewish Inscriptions of Western Europe\u003C/i>, 2 vols (Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, 1993)\u003C/span>",[6,129,295,355,416,487,538,583,629,710,768,817,859,907,941,990,1033,1066,1099,1132,1163,1194],{"file":7,"uri":7,"title":8,"status":9,"editionAuthor":11,"type":12,"objectType":16,"material":20,"condition":24,"layoutDesc":26,"handNote":35,"date":53,"places":57,"geo":66,"country":70,"region":71,"settlement":63,"repository":72,"idno":76,"textLang":79,"facsimile":86,"provenance":59,"letterHeights":93,"publications":94,"zotero":106,"keywords":118,"html":128},"ISic000781","Funerary inscription of Aurelius Samohil",{"_":10},"draft",null,{"_":13,"ana":14,"ref":15},"funerary","#function.funerary","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html",{"_":17,"ana":18,"ref":19},"plaque","#object.plaque","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259.html",{"_":21,"ana":22,"ref":23},"marble (white)","#material.stone.marble","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html",{"ana":25},"#condition.complete",{"layout":27},{"p":28,"rs":29,"damage":33},"A single line of Hebrew is followed by 14 lines of Latin; the Latin text observes a more or less regular left margin, irregular on the right. The lower right and left corners contain small incised menorahs, with the last line of text between them consisting simply of 'overspill' from the preceding line, offset towards the right.",{"_":30,"ana":31,"ref":32},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"ana":34},"#text-condition.legible",{"lettering":36,"dimensions":37},"Letters generally neatly and regularly cut, with basic serifs on the long strokes. B is somewhat irregular in fomration, sometimes with equal loops, sometimes with smaller upper loop; C is large and open; E is narrow, with three short equal horizontal strokes; G has distinctive form of small C with a tail descending to lower right; M is formed of four equal diagonal strokes; P has a somewhat elongated frequently (but not always) closed loop, but some instances have a wide horizaontal foot also; Q is closed with a trailing tail;  R is usually closed, with a tail usually straight and extended but finishing above the line; S is frequently oversize. The two menorahs at the foot of the inscription are 15 mm and 23 mm (the left is incomplete).",[38,44,49],{"type":39,"l":40,"from":41,"to":41,"h":42,"unit":43},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","7-15","mm",{"type":39,"l":45,"from":46,"to":47,"h":48,"unit":43},"Lines 2-15","line2","line15","9-19",{"type":50,"l":51,"from":41,"to":46,"h":52,"unit":43},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","not measured",{"_":54,"notBefore":55,"notAfter":55,"evidence":56},"383 CE",383,"internal-date",[58,62],{"_":59,"type":60,"ref":61},"Catina","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462270",{"_":63,"type":64,"ref":65},"Catania","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2525068",[67],[68,69],37.49223,15.07041,"Italy","Sicily",{"_":73,"role":74,"ref":75},"Museo Civico di Catania","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/018",{"_":77,"type":78},"540","inventory",{"_":80,"mainLang":81,"otherLangs":82,"languages":83},"Latin and Hebrew","la","heb",[84,85],"Latin","Hebrew",{"n":87,"url":88,"height":89,"width":90,"desc":91,"surfaceType":92},"screen","ISic000781_tiled.tif","2856px","4272px","Photo by students of Liceo Lazzaro, 2017-05-11","front",[],[95,96,96,97,98,99,100,101,102,103,104,105],"L'année épigraphique: revue des publications épigraphiques relatives a l'antiquité romaine., 1888-","Supplementum epigraphicum graecum, 1923-","Korhonen, 2004, IMusCatania","Libertini, 1929, Epigrafe giudaico-latina rinvenuta in Catania","CIJ, 1936-1952","Wilson, 1990, Sicily under the Roman Empire: the archaeology of a Roman province, 36 B.C. - A.D. 535","Manganaro, 1993, Greco nei pagi e latino nelle città della Sicilia romana tra I e VI sec. d.C.","Noy, 1993, Jewish inscriptions of Western Europe","Grüll, 2000, \" Conquerors, Patriarchs and the Law of the Lord\". Interpretation of a late antique Jewish epitaph","Manganaro, 2004-2005, Giudei grecanici nella Sicilia di eta imperale (documentazione epigrafica e figurativa)","Giuffrida, 2020, Aurelius Samohil between ius and identity",[107,108,108,109,110,111,112,113,114,115,116,117],"R46KDTZX","F2GG87EQ","2EUC82DH","Q7I7M6C5","ACIZXQF2","VF9MMBI9","JBI7CI5R","IBA4JMAN","ZCRPNPUD","BMHLMJAM","KISJUYBW",[119,120,121,13,17,21,122,123,124,125,123,126,127,81],"isic000781","funerary inscription of aurelius samohil",{"_":10},"catina","catania","italy","sicily","museo civico di catania","latin and hebrew","Text encoding: Jonathan Prag",{"file":130,"uri":130,"title":131,"status":132,"editionAuthor":11,"type":134,"objectType":135,"material":137,"condition":141,"layoutDesc":142,"handNote":146,"date":245,"places":250,"geo":257,"country":70,"region":71,"settlement":255,"repository":261,"idno":264,"textLang":266,"facsimile":270,"provenance":252,"letterHeights":275,"publications":276,"zotero":281,"keywords":286,"html":294},"ISic001155","Funerary inscription for Gaios Seios Ptolemaios",{"_":133},"edited",{"_":13,"ana":14,"ref":15},{"_":17,"ana":18,"ref":136},"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/263.html",{"_":138,"ana":139,"ref":140},"stone (grey)","#material.stone","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/2.html","",{"layout":143},{"p":144,"rs":145,"damage":141},"Four lines of Ancient Greek text. Text is contained within right side of tabula ansata. Text is centred on stone.",{"_":30,"ana":31,"ref":32},{"lettering":147,"dimensions":233},[148,149],"Greek text is straight, with crisp and well-defined letter forms. Extremely regular in layout and in spaces between letters. Serifs used on most letters. The middle lines of epsilons are formed as right-